Show Bash current state:ph_check_app_name -s -a Bash | more
Show Bash run account:ph_get_app_user Bash
Start or switch to Bash:startbash.sh | more
Stop Bash:stopbash.sh force | more
Restart Bash:restartbash.sh | more
Update Bash to the latest version (only if installed as a package):ph_update_pkg $PH_BASH_PKG_NAME | more
List all available options for Bash:confopts_ph.sh -p list -a Bash | more
View the value of any Bash option(s) (Variable expansion disabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a Bash -g
View the value of any Bash option(s) (Variable expansion enabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a Bash -g -r
View/Change the value of read-write Bash option(s) (Variable expansion disabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a Bash -s
View/Change the value of read-write Bash option(s) (Variable expansion enabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a Bash -s -r
Set all Bash options back to default:ph_set_all_options_to_default Bash
Display help for Bash option(s) (Variable expansion disabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a Bash -d
Display help for Bash option(s) (Variable expansion enabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a Bash -d -r
Display TTY currently allocated to Bash:confapps_ph.sh -p tty -a Bash | more
Move Bash to another TTY:confapps_ph.sh -p move -a Bash -t prompt
Go to Main menu:ph_show_menu Main
Go to Apps menu:ph_show_menu Apps
Open Shell to home directory (Type 'CTRL-D' to return):cd;/bin/bash
Return to previous screen:return
